Preheat #oven{} to 425 degrees.

Wash and dry all produce. In a #small pot{}, combine @Jasmine Rice{3/4%cup}, half
the @Chicken Stock Concentrate{2} (you'll use the rest later), 1 1/4 cups water (2¼
cups for 4 servings), and @Turmeric{1%tsp} (½ tsp for 4; we sent more). Bring to
a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.
Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, halve, core, and slice @Poblano Pepper{1} into ½-inch-thick strips. Halve,
peel, and cut @Yellow Onion{1} into ½-inch-thick wedges; mince a few wedges until
you have 2 TBSP (3 TBSP for 4 servings). Toss poblano and onion wedges on a
#baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @Olive Oil{3%tbsp}, @salt{} and @pepper{}.
Roast on top rack until softened and lightly charred, ~{18-20%minutes}.

While veggies roast, finely dice @Roma Tomato{1}(finely diced). Zest 1 @Lemon{2};
quarter lemons. Mince @Garlic{2%cloves}(minced). Finely chop @Cilantro{1/4%oz}.
Thinly slice @Chili Pepper{1}.

== Chimichurri ==

In a #small bowl{}, combine cilantro, half the garlic, half the @Cumin{1%tsp}
(you'll use the rest later), and juice from 1 lemon (2 lemons for 4 servings).
Add as much lemon zest and chili as you like. Stir in 2 TBSP olive oil (4 TBSP for
4); season generously with salt and pepper.

In a separate small bowl, combine tomato, minced onion, and lemon juice to taste.
Season with salt and pepper.

== Chicken ==

Pat @Chicken Breast Strips{10%oz} dry with #paper towels{}; season with salt,
pepper, and remaining cumin. Heat a drizzle of olive oil in a #large pan{} over
medium-high heat. Add chicken and cook, stirring occasionally, until browned and
cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}. Stir in 2 TBSP water (4 TBSP for 4 servings) and
remaining garlic and stock concentrates until combined. Simmer until saucy,
~{1-2%minutes}. Turn off heat.

== Assembly ==

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in @Butter{1%tbsp} (2 TBSP for 4 servings) and season
with salt and pepper. Divide between bowls and top with veggies, chicken, and
salsa. Spoon chimichurri over chicken. Serve with remaining lemon wedges on
the side.

